  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "uriparser security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for uriparser is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "The package is a strictly RFC 3986 compliant URI parsing library written in C89(\u0026quot;ANSI C\u0026quot;). uriparser is cross-platform, fast, supports Unicode and is licensed under the New BSD license. There are a number of applications, libraries and hardware using uriparser, as well as bindings and 3rd-party wrappers. uriparser is packaged in major distributions.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nIn uriparser before 1.0.2, there is pointer difference truncation to int in various places.(CVE-2026-44927)\n\nIn uriparser before 1.0.2, the function family EqualsUri can misclassify two unequal URIs as equal.(CVE-2026-44928)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for uriparser is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of low. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Low",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "uriparser",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
